22/02/2006
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Prime Minister Sergey Stanishev is warning against attempts to incite ethnic tension in the country.
In comments Tuesday (21 February), he specified that his warning referred to both the Bulgarian extreme national formation Attack, as well as to an emerging ethnic Turkish movement, Millet Trakia, which has been making radical demands.
Stanishev said he expects relevant security and judicial authorities to protect constitutional order.
(Sega - 22/02/06;
BNR, Mediapool - 21/02/06)
